---
By: William Penn
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 284
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Kindness/Gentleness
---
I suspect to pass through life but once. If therefore there be any kindness
I can show, or any good thing I can do to my fellow-being, let me do it now,
and not defer or neglect it, as I shall not pass this way again.
